commit.message: Update Travis CI job & add GHC 8.2.1

Modernise .cabal file

The 0.6.8.1 release was rather pointless, as it both redundant and
didn't have any benefit, as it didn't perform any semantic changes
that wouldn't also be possible by .cabal revisions.

Moroever, it missed the opportunity to clean up the
`.cabal` file and fix a few minor issues. This commit tries to rectify
this, so that the next proper release can contain these cleanups.

NB: There is no need to release this `.cabal` change to Hackage until
    there's other relevant changes that force a release.

Fix Base constraint, remove support for »old base«

Since support for GHC <= 7.2 was recently dropped, the Base constraint
was incorrect (…it was before as well, claiming any base >= 3 would
work).

Resolves #13
Thanks @hvr
Update Travis config to include GHC 8
